overline is the line that has 6-9 stones in a row.
There cannot exist any line longer than 9.
so, 9 is the longest possible overline.
Black is not allowed to play overline point.
Now, we know there are 3 types of forbidden moves,
But the overline is different from the previous two in one important aspect.
once the nearly overline structure exists on the board,
And that makes black defense complicated.
Black can only defend white lines which attempt to attack the overline point.
Black has no choice but to defend.
black will get very uncomfortable situation because of potential overline.
And in many cases, white can exploit the overline point in many ways,
getting good stones for himself, while black has nearly forced moves only.
Most people can find VCF wins related to overline.
This is the typical question we need to ask ourselves every time..
we know we need to block at k6,

We do not play a four unless we have to.
So, every time, no matter the reason,
you need FIRST try to see if you can do WITHOUT four
and probably gave extra stone for black etc
and limited your own tactical possibilities later and so on
We have two concerns about not playing a four here
one - we worry black goes f7
two - we worry black can play a four to either g6 and f6 and maybe its not good for us
If these two reasons turn out to be false,
then white didnt have to play a four in move 18
So, if it was my tournament game,
I would start analysing these two conditions,
and compare the outcomes with having four played first

But what are the black weaknesses?
the second weakness is the lack of inner structures
lets consider 19th stone and the probable following space move,
to be a seemingly strong attack,
but without inner structures support, its useless.
Do you rememeber we discussed the inner structures before?
So, do you think black's inner structures are good here?
indeed, they are not good at all,
So, black has no good space move here,
because white would not block the space move,
but more likely it would cut off the support
or even think of active moves
So, maybe black will balance here,
trying to build some support first.
Black gives up the pair 15_17, in order to get better inner support.
This time the attack is strong.
The inner stone 21 is more valuable for black than the line 15_17.
Because, the inner stone serves multiple purposes,
then, it cuts away the white line 18_10_14
becaise after such 21th move, the black's overline is safe,
which allows black develop without worry
furthermore, the stone 21 is beside stone 18,
which makes the 18 become a weakened defense stone
for example, in other case 24_18 would be an active pair
but now thanks to stone 21, its dead.
stone 21 , made the G-line to be the black powerline
before it belonged to whites, because of stone 8
how does it secure the overline?
move 21 gives some life to stone 11,
which would have been a waste otherwise
now the stone 11 has a chance to support black's attack.
the i8 starts to support blacks
So, the move 21 had so many clear and hidden meanings.
While many players think the open pair such as 15_17 should be valued,
I think, the good inner support is ften worth more,
especially when that pair is worthless if we dont have inner support.
So, as you see, black's tactics here was to play inner stone,
to secure the situation around the overline.
and then move 23 can develop freely.

Now black is forced to be in tight defense,

As you see, white attacked overline from two angles,
and that why overline is a big weakness for black
